{"edits":[{"content":"The criticism conflates a falsification test with an experimental dial. The forbidden cases are specified as rubric-level refuters, not harness arms. The proposal's scope is a declared applicability region; the forbidden cases are counterfactual probes chosen to falsify the monotonic inequality. Clause (2) requires that a forbidden case be measurable; a case can be measurable via controlled proxies (prompting the critic toward low precision / high recall) or via held-out slices with empirically near-target parameters, not only by direct randomization of latent population parameters. Forbidden case 3 is not self-defeating: it deliberately targets the excluded low-error regime to falsify the ceiling-attrition claim (if strict improvement >0.02 is observed there, the exclusion is invalid). Forbidden case 4 is measurable as a meta-stability check across two replications, which is a concrete empirical outcome of running the harness twice and comparing frontiers. Therefore the design satisfies clause (2) because each forbidden case is measurable either directly or via the specified proxies and held-out slices.","changed_fields":["conclusion"]}]}